                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.30 Asiatic Fleet/469: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The First Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Salisbury</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-28T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 28, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 28—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>472. Embassy’s 466, July 26 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>], 9 a.m. Following from
                    Chefoo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 27, 10 p.m. Your July 27, 9 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m</hi>.]
                            Commander-in-Chief of Asiatic Fleet authorized terms of settlement and
                            asked me to settle incident. Full report mailed yesterday.<note n="17"
                                xml:id="d187fn17">Not printed.</note> In future Embassy will be
                            notified of such incidents immediately and its instructions awaited.
                            Sorry I did not understand Embassy wanted this.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Chefoo is being instructed to mail to Tokyo for record copy of report mentioned
                    above.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Salisbury</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
